transcript.text: Welcome to own Print Shop.
In this tutorial, we'll walk you through how to set up impactful promotions like Buy X Get XBXGX and explore the latest enhancements to the Reward Points feature.
These powerful tools are part of our version 12.1 update aimed at helping you drive more sales, boost customer engagement, and build long term loyalty.
Let's dive in and see how you can make the most of these features.
To get started with setting up the BOGO or Buy X Get XBXGX offer, navigate to the admin panel, go to the Orders section, open the Coupon and Discounts menu and click on the Add button.
Enter the title of the offer, which will be visible to customers in the shopping cart.
Select the new discount type, either BOGO or BXGX, and configure the start and end dates.
Choose the applicable products and set the offer criteria such as by 1 quantity and get one quantity at 100% off or by 5 get 3 at 50% off.
Then select the user's eligible for the offer, optionally defined the order count.
Mark the promotion as active and click Save.
To see how the customer experience works.
Head over to the front store.
Add an applicable product with appropriate quantity, for example one unit, to the cart.
On the shopping cart page, customers will see a link to the available offer.
Clicking this link will open a pop up showing the offer details.
The product already in the cart will be marked with a cart icon and the customer can then select another product to pair with the deal.
Once products are in the cart, the discount is automatically applied.
For instance, in a scenario of 100% off 1 products, price will drop to 0.
This way, admins can create an offer by xget X or by xget Y promotions seamlessly.
In addition, the combo discount UI has also been revamped.
Now, discounts are clearly shown on the cart.
Products and eligible combo items are displayed in a pop up to help customers easily complete the promotional bundle.
To improve the reward redemption process and provide a more seamless checkout experience, the reward points system has been enhanced.
Customers can now directly apply their reward points at checkout without the need for generating a separate coupon code.
For the reward points setup, go to the Admin panel, navigate to the Order section and select the Reward Points menu.
On the main screen, click the Reward Points Settings button located in the top right corner.
The How Customers can Spend Their Reward Points section has been enhanced by removing the older option of redeeming points through coupon code generation.
Now, customers can directly redeem their reward points on the checkout page, making the process smoother and more user friendly without the extra step of applying a coupon.
With these upgraded features, you can seamlessly turn promotions into profits while offering greater value and convenience to your customers.
If you have any questions, our support executives are here to help.
Just reach out through live chatononprintshop.com.
Thanks for tuning in.
